results.lead_paragraph: Soviet-American cooperation in space may have proved impossible thus far for political reasons. But by design or default, a kind of cooperation may be developing in a tendency for the two nations to take different paths of space exploration in the next few years rather that duplicate each other's efforts.

results.snippet: MOSCOW, Jan. 24 -- A cosmonaut who took a "walk" in space in March, 1965, Col. Aleksei A. Leonov, dismissed with a quip today the incident two days ago in which a man fired several shots at a car occupied by himself and three fellow astronauts.
